message.content:
Below is one systematic way to “read off” the finished model from the photos and match it to the block‐dictionary images.  I have broken the analysis into three parts as requested:

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
1)  DESCRIBE THE MAIN TARGET IMAGE
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
•  Overall Count and Layers  
   –  The structure sits on four red arches (two arches on the left side and two on the right).  
   –  Above these arches are a row of colored cubes and rectangular pillars (green, red, blue, yellow, orange), plus two yellow half‐cylinders in the center‐right.  
   –  Two “house‐like” tops are formed by placing orange wedge‐shaped blocks on top of cubes (one “house” has a blue‐cube base, the other an orange‐cube base).  
   –  Several tall pillars (in green and yellow) stand behind the cubes, giving a second/third layer at the rear.

•  Spatial Relationships (left to right)
   –  Left pair of red arches (Block 1) forms the base; on top of them sit (in a row) a green cube, a red cube, a blue cube (topped by an orange wedge for a “roof”), and a yellow cube.  Behind those are a tall green pillar and a tall yellow pillar.  
   –  Right pair of red arches (Block 1) also forms a base; above them:  
       •  a green cube and two yellow half‐cylinders side‐by‐side in front,  
       •  an orange cube with an orange wedge roof (the second “house”),  
       •  behind these are another tall green pillar and two tall yellow pillars.

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
2)  SELECT (AND LIST) THE REQUIRED DICTIONARY BLOCKS
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Matching each visible piece to its dictionary index and orientation (no rotations allowed other than as shown in the dictionary images):

•  4 × Red Arch  → Dictionary #1  
•  1 × Blue Cube → Dictionary #3  
•  2 × Green Cube → Dictionary #4  
•  1 × Orange Cube → Dictionary #5  
•  1 × Red Cube → Dictionary #6  
•  2 × Yellow Cube → Dictionary #7  
•  2 × Green Tall Rectangular Pillar → Dictionary #8  
•  3 × Yellow Tall Rectangular Pillar → Dictionary #11  
•  2 × Yellow Half‐Cylinder → Dictionary #12  
•  2 × Orange Wedge (roof) → Dictionary #15  

In total, that makes 20 blocks.

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
3)  RECOMMENDED ASSEMBLY ORDER
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
A simple bottom‐to‐top, left‐to‐right build sequence might be:

{
  Step1:  Move block with index 1    // Left arch #1
  Step2:  Move block with index 1    // Left arch #2
  Step3:  Move block with index 4    // Green cube on left arch
  Step4:  Move block with index 6    // Red cube next to green
  Step5:  Move block with index 3    // Blue cube next to red
  Step6:  Move block with index 15   // Orange wedge roof atop blue cube
  Step7:  Move block with index 7    // Yellow cube next to blue
  Step8:  Move block with index 8    // Tall green pillar (rear left)
  Step9:  Move block with index 11   // Tall yellow pillar (rear left)
  Step10: Move block with index 1    // Right arch #1
  Step11: Move block with index 1    // Right arch #2
  Step12: Move block with index 4    // Green cube on right arches
  Step13: Move block with index 12   // 1st yellow half‐cylinder
  Step14: Move block with index 12   // 2nd yellow half‐cylinder
  Step15: Move block with index 5    // Orange cube for second "house"
  Step16: Move block with index 15   // Orange wedge roof (2nd "house")
  Step17: Move block with index 8    // Tall green pillar (rear right)
  Step18: Move block with index 11   // Tall yellow pillar (rear right)
  Step19: Move block with index 11   // Second tall yellow pillar (rear right)
  Step20: Move block with index 7    // Final yellow cube (if needed on right side)
}

Following the above placement yields the same layout and appearance as in the target photo, using only the unrotated blocks from the dictionary.
